Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper is primarily focused on stochastic service guarantee analysis of computer networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the analysis of traffic and service models, which can be considered as information-theoretic problems. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the properties of the proposed models, such as delay bound and backlog bound, which are related to control systems. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents models and results based on the cumulative packet inter-arrival time and the cumulative packet service time, which can be considered as data structures. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper deals with the stochastic service guarantee analysis of computer networks, which is related to performance evaluation.
